DAY 3 – Linux File System & Navigation

🧠 Notes

Today I learned how Linux is structured like a tree system starting from the root directory /.

Important directories:

* / → Root directory (starting point)
* /home → User files
* /etc → Configuration files
* /var → Logs and system data
* /tmp → Temporary files
* /bin → Essential commands

I also learned navigation commands:

* pwd → Show current location
* ls → List files
* cd → Change directory

Understanding Linux structure is important for cybersecurity because attackers often hide files in system directories.
